      <section eId="sec_CHC-878">
        <num>CHC 878</num>
        <heading>878.  Order of adjudication hearing</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-878__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The normal order of an adjudication hearing shall be:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-878__subsec_A__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Presentation of evidence offered by the state.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-878__subsec_A__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Presentation of evidence offered on behalf of the child.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-878__subsec_A__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Presentation of evidence to rebut evidence offered on behalf of the child.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-878__subsec_A__subsec_4">
            <num>(4)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Closing arguments of counsel.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-878__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>With consent of counsel, the order may be varied.  When the child is not represented by counsel, the order may not be varied.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-878__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The court may permit opening statements of the state and of counsel representing the child.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=73469</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
